      "message": "ssue #1: Missing error handling for Redfish.Patch operation\nLocation: Line 404 in gui/gui_test/security_and_access_menu/test_policies_sub_menu.robot\n\nIssue: The Redfish.Patch operation in teardown has no error handling. If it fails, the system may be left in an inconsistent state with no indication of the failure.\n\nFix: Add error handling and status code validation\n```\nTRY\n    Redfish.Patch  ${REDFISH_BASE_URI}AccountService\n    ...  body\u003d{\"HTTPBasicAuth\":${basic_auth_state}}\n    ...  valid_status_codes\u003d[${HTTP_OK}]\nEXCEPT  AS  ${error}\n    Log  Failed to restore Basic Auth state: ${error}  level\u003dWARN\nEND\n```\n\nWhy: Teardown failures should be logged but not cause test failures. Silent failures make debugging difficult.",
